%description:
Deterministic MLDv1 host-behavior test (RFC 2710).

Tests all four host behaviors via Cmdenv log assertions with a fixed RNG seed.
Membership is driven by real apps (UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path.

HOST-01 (unsolicited Report on join):
  host1 and host2 run UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1:2:3".  The socket
  join at t=0 fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> Mldv1::multicastGroupJoined
  -> unsolicited Multicast Listener Report sent immediately.

HOST-03 (report suppression):
  Both hosts join the same group and both send unsolicited Reports at t=0.
  Because all nodes are on the SAME Ethernet segment (via EthernetHub), host2
  hears host1's Report while host2 is still in DELAYING_LISTENER state.
  host2 suppresses its own pending timer (cancelEvent, flag=false,
  state=IDLE_LISTENER). The test asserts the "received Multicast Listener
  Report" log line from host2, proving the suppression path was exercised.

HOST-02 (delayed Report on General Query):
  The router has multicastForwarding=true (real querier). With
  startupQueryInterval=2s the router sends its first General MLD Query at ~t=2s
  (type=130, multicastAddress=::, maxRespDelay=1000ms) to ff02::1.
  All nodes on the shared Ethernet segment receive it. Hosts receive it via
  processMldMessage -> processQuery -> processGroupQuery. Idle Listeners
  transition to Delaying Listener and schedule uniform(0, 1s) delayed Reports.
  The test asserts the "received General Listener Query" log line from host1
  and then a subsequent "sending Multicast Listener Report".

HOST-04 (Done on leave):
  BOTH hosts' UdpSinks have stopTime=5s. On close, ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal ->
  Mldv1::multicastGroupLeft sends a Done ONLY if the host holds flag=true. Exactly one
  host is the reporter (holds flag=true after the Query race) -- host1 at the pinned
  seed -- so host1 sends the Done and host2 leaves silently. The test asserts host1's
  Done and, as a %not-contains, that host2 sends none. This is the seed-pinned form of
  the relational property "the host that Reported is the one that sends the Done".

Network: host1, host2, and router all connect to a shared EthernetHub, putting
them on the same Ethernet segment. Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses.
All three nodes have hasMld=true. The router is a real querier (router.multicastForwarding
enabled -- set at node level so NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates it to the routing table)
with short startup timer so the General Query arrives within the 10s limit.
The RNG seed is pinned (see the seed-set note below): an RNG shift swaps which host wins
the race, so the seed may need re-picking so host1 stays the reporter.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldHostBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        host2: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        host2.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldHostBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 10s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# MLDv1 answers a General Query after a random uniform(0, maxRespDelay) delay; when two hosts share
# a group, the shorter delay reports first and the other suppresses (Mldv1.cc:311 and :410). So
# which host ends up as the reporter -- and therefore holds flag=true and sends the Done on leave --
# is an RNG coin flip. opp_test cannot express the relational property "the reporter is the host that
# sends the Done, and the other sends none", so we PIN the seed to fix the roles: at seed 1 host1 is
# the reporter, so host1 sends the Done and host2 (which also leaves) sends none -- exactly one Done,
# from host1, as asserted below.
# NOTE: a change elsewhere that shifts how many random numbers are drawn before this point can swap
# the roles. If that happens, re-pick a seed where host1 wins (seeds 1, 3, 4, 6 do; 0, 2, 5, 7 do
# not) -- the behavior is unchanged, only which host plays which role.
seed-set = 1

# Enable MLD on all nodes
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no 1s+ delay before addresses are ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# HOST-01/03: host1 and host2 join ff0e::1:2:3 via UdpSink (real production path).
# Socket join fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> Mldv1::multicastGroupJoined.
# On the shared Ethernet segment, each host's unsolicited Report is seen by the other,
# triggering report suppression (HOST-03).
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
# HOST-04: BOTH hosts leave at t=5s (socket close -> ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal). Only the host
# holding flag=true (the reporter, host1 at this seed) sends a Done; the suppressed host leaves
# silently. host2 also leaving is what makes "host2 sends no Done" a real check, not a tautology.
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

**.host2.numApps = 1
**.host2.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host2.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
**.host2.app[0].stopTime = 5s

# HOST-02: enable real querier on the router (multicastForwarding at node level so
# NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding
# to all submodules, overriding any per-submodule INI setting).
**.router.multicastForwarding = true
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 2s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 5s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-01: unsolicited Multicast Listener Report sent by host1 on join
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-03: report suppression -- host2 hears host1's Report for ff0e::1:2:3 while in DELAYING state
%# and cancels its own pending timer (both hosts are on the same Ethernet segment via hub)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host2.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-02: router's General Query at t=2s is received by host1
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received General Listener Query on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-02: after the General Query, host1 schedules and sends a delayed Report (within 1s)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-04: Done sent to ff02::2 when host1 leaves at t=5s (flag=true after Query-driven Report)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# CORRELATION (the other host): host2 also leaves at t=5s, but as the suppressed loser at this seed
%# it holds flag=false and sends NO Done -- only the reporter (host1) does. This is the seed-pinned
%# "the reporter sends the Done, the other does not" check. (See the seed-set note above: an RNG
%# shift swaps the roles, and the seed would need to be re-picked so host1 is the reporter again.)
%not-contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host2.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Done

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
